We find little evidence that funding availability contributes to bubble activity. However, we find that bubble activity is greater during times when the returns earned from currency risk factor portfolios are depressed. This supports the argument that herding behaviour is greater when economic agents face unattractive return alternatives. Furthermore, results suggest that currency bubbles may directly affect the returns of these investment strategies, specifically in the case of carry trade.},
